Chile's presidential race heads to runoff between communist and hard-right candidates
subhed: Jeannette Jara, 51, a communist and former labor minister representing Chile's center-left governing coalition, won 26.85% of votes with 99% counted – insufficient to win in the first round. Hard-right ex-lawmaker and devout Catholic Jose Antonio Kast, 59, secured more than 23.93%. A second round will take place on December 14.

title: What is Europe's 'fair share' of climate action compared to other countries?
subhed: Europe produces only 6% of today's global greenhouse gas emissions, a point some politicians use to play down the continent's responsibility. Scientists counter that, looking at historical emissions, Europe still has far to go to meet the Paris Agreement.

title: London's 'mudlarks' scour the Thames for treasure
subhed: On the banks of the British capital's river, London's 'mudlarks' search for fragments of the past: ancient pottery, old coins, bone dice. These enthusiasts are less motivated by the value of the objects than by the stories they tell. Sometimes, their finds even end up in a museum, as is currently being shown in an exhibition at the London Museum.
